-- Insert Reading Plan Days for "30-Day Psalms Journey"

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = '30-Day Psalms Journey'), 2, 'Finding Refuge in God', 'Psalm 46:1-3', 'God is our refuge and strength, an ever-present help in trouble. Therefore we will not fear, though the earth give way and the mountains fall into the heart of the sea, though its waters roar and foam and the mountains quake with their surging.', 'In times of uncertainty and fear, we can find our security not in our circumstances, but in God Himself. He is described as our refuge - a place of safety and protection. When everything around us seems to be falling apart, God remains our solid foundation.', 'What situations in your life currently need God''s refuge and strength?', 'Ask God to be your refuge today and to help you find peace in His presence, regardless of external circumstances.'),

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = '30-Day Psalms Journey'), 3, 'The Good Shepherd', 'Psalm 23:1-4', 'The Lord is my shepherd, I lack nothing. He makes me lie down in green pastures, he leads me beside quiet waters, he refreshes my soul. He guides me along the right paths for his name''s sake. Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil, for you are with me; your rod and your staff, they comfort me.', 'Perhaps the most beloved psalm, Psalm 23 paints a beautiful picture of God''s care for us. Like a shepherd tends his sheep, God provides for our needs, guides our paths, and protects us. Even in dark times, we don''t walk alone - our Shepherd is with us.', 'In what areas of your life do you need to trust God''s guidance and provision more fully?', 'Thank Jesus for being your Good Shepherd and ask Him to help you follow His leading in every area of your life.');

-- Insert Reading Plan Days for "Peace in Uncertain Times"

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = 'Peace in Uncertain Times'), 2, 'Perfect Peace', 'Isaiah 26:3', 'You will keep in perfect peace those whose minds are steadfast, because they trust in you.', 'God promises perfect peace to those who keep their minds focused on Him. This doesn''t mean we ignore reality or pretend problems don''t exist. Rather, it means we choose to fix our thoughts on God''s character, promises, and faithfulness instead of being consumed by our circumstances.', 'How can you practice keeping your mind steadfast on God throughout your day?', 'Pray for God to help you maintain a steadfast mind focused on Him, and ask for His perfect peace to guard your heart.'),

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = 'Peace in Uncertain Times'), 3, 'Casting All Cares', '1 Peter 5:7', 'Cast all your anxiety on him because he cares for you.', 'The word "cast" implies a deliberate action - throwing or hurling something away from yourself. God invites us to take all our worries, fears, and anxieties and throw them onto Him. Why? Because He genuinely cares for us. Our concerns matter to Him because we matter to Him.', 'What specific anxieties do you need to cast upon God right now?', 'Deliberately cast each of your worries upon God, thanking Him that He cares for you and will handle what concerns you.');

-- Insert sample days for other plans (abbreviated for space)

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = 'Wisdom Literature Deep Dive'), 1, 'The Fear of the Lord', 'Proverbs 1:7', 'True wisdom begins with a proper reverence and awe for God. This foundational principle will guide all our learning.', 'How would you describe your current relationship with God - is it characterized by reverent awe?', 'Ask God to give you a heart that fears Him in the biblical sense - with reverence, awe, and respect.'),

((SELECT id FROM reading_plans WHERE name = 'Heroes of Faith'), 1, 'Abraham''s Call', 'Genesis 12:1-4', 'Abraham''s journey of faith began with a call from God to leave everything familiar and trust in God''s promises.', 'What might God be calling you to leave behind in order to follow Him more fully?', 'Pray for the faith to follow God''s leading, even when the path is uncertain.');